    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Trivial File Transfer Protocol is a simple, lock-step, file transfer protocol which allows a client to get or put a file onto a remote host.  This document describes a simple extension to TFTP to allow option negotiation prior to the file transfer.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
